  <mads:note>Brill's New Pauly: "Parmenion, Epigrammatist from Macedonia, 15 poems survive: five of
    them are individual couplets none is longer than four stanzas. P. pursues in his poems a canon of brevity he 
    himself recommends (ibid. 9,342). The themes vary (but no votive epigrams
    one text perhaps the funerary epigram Anth. Pal. 7,184, cf. GVI 115), the style is simple.
    Identification with Parmenon, to whom Anth. Pal. 13,18 is attributed (his authorship may 
    have arisen from the name in the dedication in verse 4, cf. FGE 74), can be rejected...."
    from Albiani, Maria Grazia (Bologna). "Parmenion." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and
    Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2011. Brill Online..</mads:note>
